HEADWORD: Doucepere
<hw>Douce"pere`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>les douze
pairs</ets> the twelve peers of France, renowned in romantic
fiction.]</ety> <def>One of the twelve peers of France, companions of
Charlemagne in war.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>douzepere</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Big-looking like a doughty <qex>doucepere</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj></p>

